'''Kwame Akoto-Bamfo''' yɛ Ghanani ɛboɔ dwomfo . ɔdaa ne boɔ a ɔdwomeɛ a egyina hɔ sɛ nkaede ma wɔn a wofaa ɛyaw mu wɔo nkoasom mu a w’ato din Transatlantic slave trade, na ɛboɔ no yɛ ade ɛwɔ beae bi a wɔfrɛ no National Memorial for Peace and Justice a wobue ano wɛ afe 2018 wɔ Montgomery, Alabama. Ne boɔ a w’adwom foforo ne nea ɛyɛ 1,200 aboɔ  a egyina hɔ ma Ghana nananom nsamanfoɔ a wɔfaa nkoasom mu wɔ Accra, a ɛyɛ [[Ghana]] Kuropɔn. W’ato ne din ''Faux-Reedom'', na wɔ bue ano wɔ afe 2017.

